<HEAD>Inner-City Community Unites Behind Threatened Activist</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BOSTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Inner-city church and community activists are
offering a $10,000 reward for the names of gang members believed to
have put a $5,000 bounty on the head of an anti-drug activist.
   Georgette Watson, a founder of the Drop-A-Dime hotline for
fielding tips on drug pushers, has been under 24-hour police
protection since last week. Gang members also allegedly offered
$1,000 to anyone wounding the mother of three.
   ``We are extremely concerned about the threats made against the
