<TEXT>
   Christmas trees can get a holiday stamp of
approval from the U.S. Postal Service with special ornaments on
sale this year.
   The silverplated ornaments, which sell for $12.95 each, are
being offered in about a third of the agency's divisions across the
country or may be ordered from the Postal Service Philatelic Sales
Division in Washington.
