<HEAD>Bush Names 4 Officials to King Holiday Commission</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   President Bush has decided to name four top
government officials to be members of the Martin Luther King Jr.,
federal holiday commission in 1990.
   They are Secretaries Jack Kemp of HUD and Lauro Cavazos of
Education, and William J. Bennett, director of National Drug
Control Policy and Constance B. Newman, director of the Office of
Personnel Management.
