C. Aldridge Jr., to the president's national security
telecommunications advisory committee, and Paul F. Oreffice to the
advisory committee for trade policy and negotiations.
   Oreffice, president and chief excutive officer of the Dow
Chemical Company in Midland, Mich., is being reappointed to a
two-year term.
